## Text Processing Tools

Tools differ from GNU/POSIX counterparts (see tool-specific skills):

- **awk(1):** Plan 9 regexp engine; `-safe` flag; `utf()` built-in; no gawk
  extensions; uses rc(1) not sh for subcommands.
- **sed(1):** Plan 9 regexp; no `-i`; `-g` global flag; uses rc(1).
- **grep(1):** Plan 9 regexp; `-b` means unbuffered (not byte offset);
  `-l`/`-L`/`-c`/`-n`/`-v`/`-i`/`-h`/`-s`; no `-A`/`-B`/`-C`/`-r`/`-o`.
- **ed(1):** Plan 9 regexp; `b` is Browse not label; `P` is print not prompt.
- **sam(1):** Structural regular expressions; client-server model.

**Regular expressions (regexp(6)):** Plan 9 uses its own regexp library
(see `plan9-regexp` skill).  No `\d`, `\w`, `\s`, `\b`, no POSIX character
classes `[[:alpha:]]`, no lookahead/lookbehind, no backreferences in patterns.
Alternation is `|`; grouping is `()`.

