## File Path Conventions

    /bin         executable binaries (union of several sources)
    /rc/bin      rc scripts (often part of /bin union)
    /lib         libraries, fonts, locale data
    /sys/src     system source code
    /sys/man     manual pages
    /usr/username  user home directories
    /tmp         temporary files
    /net         network protocols
    /srv         service file descriptors
    /proc        process information
    /dev         devices
    /env         environment variables
    /fd          open file descriptors
    /mnt         mount points for applications
    /n           mount points for remote file trees

**No `/etc`:** Configuration is typically done via plan9.ini (kernel config),
ndb (network database), or factotum (authentication).  There is no
`/etc/passwd`, `/etc/shadow`, `/etc/hosts`, `/etc/resolv.conf`.

**No `/home`:** User home directories are typically `/usr/$user`.

**No `/usr/local`:** Software is generally built into `/bin`, `/lib`, etc.

