## Quick Reference: UNIX → Plan 9 Mapping

| UNIX concept            | Plan 9 equivalent                              |
|-------------------------|------------------------------------------------|
| `/bin/sh`               | `/bin/rc` (rc shell)                           |
| `$PATH`                 | `$path` (list variable); use `bind -a` for /bin|
| `fork()` + `execve()`   | `rfork(RFPROC|RFFDG|...)` + `exec()`           |
| `kill -SIGNAL pid`      | write `kill` to `/proc/pid/ctl`                |
| POSIX signals           | Notes (text strings) via `/proc/pid/note`      |
| `/etc/passwd`           | factotum + file server user lists              |
| BSD sockets             | `/net/tcp`, `/net/udp` file interface          |
| `errno`                 | `errstr()` / `%r` format verb                  |
| `exit(n)`               | `exits("reason")` (string, not int)            |
| FUSE                    | 9P user-space file servers                     |
| `setuid` bit            | Not present; use auth agent                    |
| `/dev/stdin`            | `/fd/0`                                        |
| `~/.profile`            | `$home/lib/profile`                            |
| `$HOME`                 | `$home`                                        |
| `$USER` / `whoami`      | `$user` / `cat /dev/user`                      |
| `hostname`              | `cat /dev/sysname`                             |
| `ps`                    | `ps(1)` (different flags; shows wait state)    |
| `strace`                | `acid(1)` debugger + `/proc/n/mem`             |
| `crontab`               | `cron(8)` (present but simpler)                |
| `sudo`                  | No equivalent; CPU server/auth model instead   |
| `ln -s`                 | No symbolic links on native file servers; use `bind` |
| GNU sed `-i`            | `sed '...' f > f.tmp && mv f.tmp f`           |
| `grep -r`               | `grep -r` absent; use `g` wrapper or `du -a | xargs grep` |

